solution.p:
   The maximum population is at the beginning of July, which is t=6:
   
   
	   P(6) = -5\cos\left(\frac{\pi}{6} \cdot 6 \right) + 10 = -5(-1) +10 = 15 \text{ thousand rabbits}
   .
   
   The minimum population is at the beginning of January, which is t=0:
   
	   P(0) = -5\cos\left(\frac{\pi}{6} \cdot 0 \right) + 10 = -5(1) +10 = 5 \text{ thousand rabbits}

